  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification has been performed to characterize aleatory variability in blood viscosity, RBC fragility, and inlet flow waveform; we plan to extend with sensitivity analysis in a future revision to formally rank dominant input drivers.",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-claim",
